          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "First, find your Total Daily Energy Expenditure (TDEE) — how many calories you burn per day including all activity. Then subtract the deficit you want. This calculator does this automatically using the Mifflin–St Jeor equation. For example, if your TDEE is 2,200 kcal and you want to lose 0.5 kg/week, your daily calorie target is approximately 2,200 − 550 = 1,650 kcal."
